    "department": "Client Service",
    "description": "Riveron is seeking a Senior Associate – Valuation Services to support valuation engagements for U.S. clients across financial and tax reporting, transactions, restructuring, and strategic advisory matters. This role requires a strong blend of technical valuation expertise, project management, and client-facing experience.\n\nAs a Senior Associate, you will serve as a key engagement team member, working closely with Manager, Directors and MDs, while remaining actively involved in the execution and review of valuation analyses and deliverables.\n\nQualifications:\n\n - Minimum 3+ years of progressive experience in valuation or related consulting roles.\n\n - Bachelor’s degree in Finance, Accounting, Economics, or a related field (required).\n\n - MBA with concentration in Finance or demonstrated progress towards professional credentials such as CFA, ASA, or CPA is strongly preferred.\n\n - Strong technical expertise in business valuation, intangible asset valuation, and equity valuation.\n\n - Solid understanding of U.S. GAAP valuation topics, including ASC 805, ASC 820, and other fair value measurement guidance.\n\n - Advanced financial modeling skills with a high level of proficiency in Microsoft Excel and valuation databases like Capital IQ\n\n - Demonstrated ability to manage multiple engagements and deadlines in a fast-paced professional services environment.\n\nWhat You’ll Do:\n\n - Execute valuation engagements involving business enterprises, intangible assets and equity items (i.e. shares of common stock).\n\n - Support Project Managers with end-to-end engagement oversight, including project scoping, planning, execution, review, and delivery of client-ready reports along with Project Manager.\n\n - Apply appropriate valuation methodologies such as Discounted Cash Flow (DCF), intangible asset models, option-pricing models, market-based approaches, transaction-based analyses, and other relevant techniques.\n\n - Support valuations for a variety of purposes including business combinations, goodwill and asset impairment testing, tax valuation, bankruptcy/restructuring, and strategic planning.\n\n - Drive the development of valuation models, analyses, and reports; ensuring technical accuracy and adherence to firm quality standards.\n\n - Identify and resolve engagement issues and risks, escalating matters as appropriate to project leaders.\n\n - Collaborate with MDs and Directors on engagement strategy, timelines, and client relationship management.\n\n - Foster a collaborative, high-performance team environment aligned with Riveron’s client-first and entrepreneurial culture.\n\n - Assist with engagement staffing, workload management, and coaching across multiple concurrent projects.\n\nWho You Are:\n\n - Strong analytical and critical-thinking skills.\n\n - Excellent written and verbal communication skills, including the ability to present complex valuation concepts clearly to clients.\n\n - Client-service orientation with a high level of professionalism and accountability.\n\n - Adaptability and comfort working in a dynamic, growth-oriented advisory firm.\n\n - You are willing and able to travel as required.\n\nAbout Riveron:\n\nAt Riveron, we partner with clients—from global multinationals to high-growth private entities—to solve complex finance challenges, guided by our DELTA values: Drive, Excellence, Leadership, Teamwork, and Accountability. Our entrepreneurial culture thrives on collaboration, diverse perspectives, and delivering exceptional outcomes. We are committed to fostering growth, both for our clients and our people, through mentorship, integrity, and a client-centric approach. This inclusive environment offers flexibility, progressive benefits, and meaningful opportunities for impactful work that supports well-being in and out of the office.\n\nCheck us out on social media:\n\nLinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/company/riveron/life/culture/ Glassdoor https://www.glassdoor.com/Photos/Riveron-Office-Photos-E672242.htm Instagram https://www.instagram.com/riveronconsulting/ Facebook https://www.facebook.com/RiveronConsulting/\n\nRiveron Consulting is an Equal Opportunity Employer and believes that we are stronger together through our diversity. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, age, national origin, disability status, protected veteran status, sexual orientation, gender identity or any other characteristic protected by law.\n\nFull time roles are eligible for a full range of benefits including medical, dental, and vision insurance, 401(k) with company match, and PTO. A complete description of all available benefits can be found at Riveron's Benefits page at https://riveron.com/riveron-life/. Contract roles are not eligible for benefits.\n\n\nFRAUD ALERT\n\nPlease beware of fraudulent schemes or impersonations when going through the job application process. A Riveron employee will never recruit via text or extend unsolicited employment offers. Additionally, a Riveron employee will never ask you to exchange money or purchase anything as part of the recruiting process.\n\n\nWE MAY USE ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE (AI) TOOLS TO SUPPORT PARTS OF THE HIRING PROCESS, SUCH AS REVIEWING APPLICATIONS, ANALYZING RESUMES, OR ASSESSING RESPONSES. THESE TOOLS ASSIST OUR RECRUITMENT TEAM BUT DO NOT REPLACE HUMAN JUDGMENT. FINAL HIRING DECISIONS ARE ULTIMATELY MADE BY HUMANS. IF YOU WOULD LIKE MORE INFORMATION ABOUT HOW YOUR DATA IS PROCESSED, PLEASE CONTACT US.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
